</taxonomicName>
” was already pre-occupied in the name 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFC3D28ABFADEFE0B" authority="Don (1823: 299)" authorityName="Don" authorityPageNumber="299" authorityYear="1823" box="[928,1399,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Arthrostemma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFC3D28ABFB1AFE0B" box="[928,1203,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Arthrostemma latifolium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFB2728AAFADEFE0B" author="Don, D." box="[1210,1399,446,473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="276 - 329" refId="ref8934" refString="Don, D. (1823) An illustration of the natural family of plants called Melastomaceae. Memoirs of the Wernerian Natural History Society 4: 276 - 329." type="journal article" year="1823">Don (1823: 299)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC1E36CBFFEDFFAEFF2028F7FF69FD07" blockId="4.[136,1452,374,1193]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
While describing 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFE1B28F6FCA5FE2E" authority="Naudin, Naudin (1850)" authorityName="Naudin, Naudin" authorityYear="1850" box="[390,780,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tetrameris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFE1B28F6FE57FE2F" box="[390,510,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Tetrameris</emphasis>
Naudin, Naudin (1850)
</taxonomicName>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFC0828F6FBA3FE2F" authorityName="Triana" authorityYear="1872" baseAuthorityName="DC." box="[917,1034,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Comolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aubletii">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFC0828F6FBA3FE2F" box="[917,1034,482,509]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">A. aubletii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to this genus, using the same epithet as 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFF3B2B12FE2DFDF3" author="De Candolle, A. P." box="[166,388,518,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" refId="ref8849" refString="De Candolle, A. P. (1828) Melastomaceae. In: De Candolle, A. P. (Ed.) Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, sive enumeratio contracta ordinum, generum, specierumque plantarum huc usque cognitarum, juxta methodi naturalis normas digesta. Vol. 3. Sumptibus Sociorum Treuttel et Wurtz, Parisiis [Paris], pp. 99 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 286" type="book" year="1828">De Candolle (1828)</bibRefCitation>
, and established the new combination 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFCAD2B12FB68FDF3" authority="(DC.) Naudin. According" authorityName="Naudin. According" baseAuthorityName="DC." box="[816,1217,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Comolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aubletii">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFCAD2B12FC09FDF3" box="[816,928,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">T. aubletii</emphasis>
(DC.) Naudin. According
</taxonomicName>
to Article 11.4 of the ICN, Naudin (1850) should have used the epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFD272B3FFCBAFD97" authorityName="Aublet" authorityYear="1775" box="[698,787,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFD272B3FFCBAFD97" box="[698,787,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">latifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in such combination due to its priority, since 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFA8B2B3FFF5CFDBB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Arthostemma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFA8B2B3FFF5CFDBB" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Arthostemma latifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not combined in 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFE622B5AFDDEFDBB" authorityName="Naudin, Naudin" authorityYear="1850" box="[511,631,591,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tetrameris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFE622B5AFDDEFDBB" box="[511,631,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Tetrameris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFD142B5BFC8EFDBB" author="Triana, J. J." box="[649,807,590,616]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="1 - 188" refId="ref10852" refString="Triana, J. J. (1872) I. Les Melastomacees. The transactions of the Linnean Society of London 28: 1 - 188. http: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1871. tb 00222. x" type="journal article" year="1872">Triana (1872)</bibRefCitation>
also used the epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFBA42B5BFB26FDBB" box="[1081,1167,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Comolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aubletii">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFBA42B5BFB26FDBB" box="[1081,1167,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">aubletii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” when he transferred 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFA0A2B5AFF77FD5F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Comolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aubletii">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFA0A2B5AFF77FD5F" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">T. aubletii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFE9D2B67FEC9FD5F" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[256,352,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Comolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFE9D2B67FEC9FD5F" box="[256,352,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Comolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Like Naudin (1850), 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFDCA2B67FD59FD5F" author="Triana, J. J." box="[599,752,626,652]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="1 - 188" refId="ref10852" refString="Triana, J. J. (1872) I. Les Melastomacees. The transactions of the Linnean Society of London 28: 1 - 188. http: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1871. tb 00222. x" type="journal article" year="1872">Triana (1872)</bibRefCitation>
should have used the epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFBDE2B67FB35FD5F" authorityName="Aublet" authorityYear="1775" box="[1091,1180,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFBDE2B67FB35FD5F" box="[1091,1180,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">latifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in its new combination for the same reason as their predecessor, since this epithet could be used in 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFC412B83FB95FD63" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[988,1084,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Comolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFC412B83FB95FD63" box="[988,1084,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Comolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, according to Article 11.4 of the ICN.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC1E36CBFFEDFFAEFF202BCBFF69FBCB" blockId="4.[136,1452,374,1193]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
Finally, when elaborating his treatment in 
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFD012BCBFCCCFD2B" box="[668,869,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Flora brasiliensis</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFCE92BCBFB9DFD2A" author="Cogniaux, A." box="[884,1076,734,761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" refId="ref8702" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1885) Melastomaceae. Tribus II. Tibouchineae Baill. In: Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas. Vol. 14. Frid. Fleischer, Monachii et Lipsiae [Munich &amp; Leipzig], pp. 205 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book" year="1885">Cogniaux (1885)</bibRefCitation>
made the correct combination of 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFF152A17FED2FCCF" authority="Aubl." authorityName="Aublet" authorityYear="1775" box="[136,379,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFF152A17FE9FFCCF" box="[136,310,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Rhexia latifolia</emphasis>
Aubl.
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFE3D2A17FCA1FCCF" authority="(Aubl.) Cogn." authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Aubl." box="[416,776,770,797]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Comolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFE3D2A17FDC8FCCF" box="[416,609,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Comolia latifolia</emphasis>
(Aubl.) Cogn.
</taxonomicName>
, according to Article 11.4 of the ICN. However, the original material of this species has not been located (
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFD122A33FCE8FC92" author="Cogniaux, A." box="[655,833,806,833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" refId="ref8702" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1885) Melastomaceae. Tribus II. Tibouchineae Baill. In: Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas. Vol. 14. Frid. Fleischer, Monachii et Lipsiae [Munich &amp; Leipzig], pp. 205 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book" year="1885">Cogniaux 1885</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFCD32A33FC45FC93" author="Howard, R. A." box="[846,1004,806,832]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="255 - 292" refId="ref9343" refString="Howard, R. A. (1983) The plates of Aublet's histoire des plantes de la Guiane Francoise. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 64: 255 - 292." type="journal article" year="1983">Howard 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFC642A33FB0BFC93" author="Wurdack, J. J." box="[1017,1186,806,832]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="82 - 89" refId="ref11350" refString="Wurdack, J. J. (1993) Comolia DC. In: Gorts-van Rijn, A. R. A. &amp; Jansen-Jacobs, M. J. (Eds.) The Flora of the Guianas: 99. Melastomataceae. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, pp. 82 - 89." type="book chapter" year="1993">Wurdack 1993</bibRefCitation>
), but was likely sent to BM, as was the case with the original material of 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFD2D2A5FFC3DFCB7" authority="Aubl." authorityName="Aubl." box="[688,916,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFD2D2A5FFCE6FCB7" box="[688,847,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Rhexia villosa</emphasis>
Aubl.
</taxonomicName>
[collected in the same location by Jean Baptiste Christophe Fusée Aublet (1720–1778) and described in the same treatment]. Thus far, the collection has not been found in the herbaria consulted, so we cannot comment on its whereabouts (e.g., if it was lost, destroyed or destined for another institution that was not consulted). Thus, the illustration (see 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFC302AA3FBEFFC02" author="Aublet, J. B. C. F." box="[941,1094,950,977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" refId="ref8307" refString="Aublet, J. B. C. F. (1775 a) Histoire des plantes de la Guiane Francoise, rangees suivant la methode sexuelle, avec plusieurs memoires: sur differens objets interessans, relatifs a la Culture et au Commerce de la Guiane Francoise &amp; une Notice des Plantes de l'Islede-France. Ouvrage orne de pres de quatre cents planches en taille-douce, ou sont representees des plantes qui n'ont point encore ete decrites ni gravees, ou qui ne l'ont ete qu'imparfaitement. Vol. 3. Chez Pierre-Francois Didot jeune, Libraire de la Faculte de Medecine, Quai des Augustins, Londres &amp; Paris, 193 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 674" type="book" year="1775">Aublet 1775a</bibRefCitation>
) mentioned in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="0BA14D48FFEDFFAEFF152ACFFE74FC26" authority="(Aublet 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Aublet" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[136,477,986,1013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Rhexia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFF152ACFFE9EFC27" box="[136,311,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Rhexia latifolia</emphasis>
(Aublet 1775)
</taxonomicName>
is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="131A8869FFEDFFAEFD552ACFFC86FC27" box="[712,815,986,1012]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">lectotype</typeStatus>
of this name (
<figureCitation id="549A2A4EFFEDFFAEFC4F2ACFFB9AFC27" box="[978,1075,986,1012]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1338,1360]" captionTargetBox="[386,1202,244,1314]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[386,1202,244,1314]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Reproduction of the original illustration of Comolia latifolia (Aubl.) Cogn. (inside the red square), published in Aublet (1775a, pl. 129, fig. 2)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423979" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423979/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Figure 3</figureCitation>
), according to Article 9.11 of the ICN.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC1E36CBFFEDFFAEFF202D37FC43FB7B" blockId="4.[136,1452,374,1193]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
The fact that the original material has not yet been located has raised some questions about the true identity of this taxon (
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFE972D53FE14FBB2" author="Cogniaux, A." box="[266,445,1094,1121]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" refId="ref8702" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1885) Melastomaceae. Tribus II. Tibouchineae Baill. In: Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas. Vol. 14. Frid. Fleischer, Monachii et Lipsiae [Munich &amp; Leipzig], pp. 205 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book" year="1885">Cogniaux 1885</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFE562D53FDDFFBB3" author="Wurdack, J. J." box="[459,630,1094,1120]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="82 - 89" refId="ref11350" refString="Wurdack, J. J. (1993) Comolia DC. In: Gorts-van Rijn, A. R. A. &amp; Jansen-Jacobs, M. J. (Eds.) The Flora of the Guianas: 99. Melastomataceae. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, pp. 82 - 89." type="book chapter" year="1993">Wurdack 1993</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFD112D53FCE4FBB2" author="Cogniaux, A." box="[652,845,1094,1121]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" refId="ref8702" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1885) Melastomaceae. Tribus II. Tibouchineae Baill. In: Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas. Vol. 14. Frid. Fleischer, Monachii et Lipsiae [Munich &amp; Leipzig], pp. 205 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book" year="1885">Cogniaux (1885)</bibRefCitation>
commented in Latin “ 
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFBC92D52FA36FBB3" box="[1108,1439,1094,1121]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Species dubia, mihi non visa</emphasis>
” – in English “ 
<emphasis id="FED5EAD9FFEDFFAEFEB92D7FFD31FB57" box="[292,664,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Doubtful species, I have not seen</emphasis>
” –, while 
<bibRefCitation id="A8304B3AFFEDFFAEFC902D7FFC6DFB57" author="Wurdack, J. J." box="[781,964,1130,1156]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="82 - 89" refId="ref11350" refString="Wurdack, J. J. (1993) Comolia DC. In: Gorts-van Rijn, A. R. A. &amp; Jansen-Jacobs, M. J. (Eds.) The Flora of the Guianas: 99. Melastomataceae. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, pp. 82 - 89." type="book chapter" year="1993">Wurdack (1993)</bibRefCitation>
also considered this species as doubtful. In agreement with the previous treatments, we consider this species as doubtful.
</paragraph>
